Steps.Message: Following on from our previous message, we can now confirm we have switched power off to 11 properties. This is to allow our engineers to safely repair an overhead network fault. If your electricity has gone off, you can keep updated by texting POWER followed by your full postcode to 80876 (e.g. POWER IP3 8AA). Standard text fees apply.

We became aware of this power cut at 18:07. We’re sorry for any disruption this may have caused you. We didn’t know in advance there would be a power cut, but now that we know, our teams will do everything they can to get your power back quickly. Engineers in our control room have switched some customers power back on in your area. To get everyone’s power back on we may need to attend to investigate and make repairs. We’ll continue to update you until everyone’s power is back on.
Steps.Name: We are restoring customers automatically

Steps.Message: We have engineers on their way. As this is affecting your area, they will not need to attend your property. Rest assured once they arrive, they’ll work as quickly as is safely possible to get your power back on.
Steps.Name: Engineers on their way

Steps.Message: Engineers are now on site, carrying out investigations into the fault. Once they have completed their assessment, they will carry out repairs.
Steps.Name: Engineers investigating and fixing
